st on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:103:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-unveils-a-refreshed-website-design-let-us-know-what-you-think/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-unveils-a-refreshed-website-design-let-us-know-what-you-think/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"How to make your WooCommerce store run faster with WP-Optimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/uJg_1JWixAI/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-make-your-woocommerce-store-run-faster-with-wp-optimize/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 08 Mar 2019 16:26:31 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP Optimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"WP-O\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP-Optimise\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WP-Optimise Update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP-Optimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"WP-Optmize update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=360816\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:801:\"<p>Page Speed is the foundation to a great online shopping experience. Of course an excellent user experience with an eye-catching store is essential, but page speed is the most crucial benchmark for any WooCommerce website. Just a one second delay &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-make-your-woocommerce-store-run-faster-with-wp-optimize/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-make-your-woocommerce-store-run-faster-with-wp-optimize/\">How to make your WooCommerce store run faster with WP-Optimize</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"wmullins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7302:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Page Speed is the foundation to a great online shopping experience. Of course an excellent user experience with an eye-catching store is essential, but page speed is the most crucial benchmark for any WooCommerce website. Just a one second delay can result in the user deciding they have had a bad user experience and create a loss of trust in the brand, which can lead to abandoned carts and increased bounce rates. This results in not just a potential loss of a sale, but far more importantly, a dissatisfied customer. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When queried on how long it should take a site to load, 47% of customers expect a load time of around 2 seconds. When it comes to WooCommerce, the chances of slower page speed is higher as there is a constant influx of new, updated products and categories being processed. While these updates are happening in the background, your database and server space is continually increasing, which can slow down your site.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the time of writing this article, the </span><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-optimize/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">WP-Optimize</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> free version plugin has more than 800,000 active installations. There is also a premium version available that includes additional features and tools for optimizing your website and WooCommerce store. We are continually working hard to make the plugin better and help solve real-world problems our users are facing in terms of site optimization. </span></p>\n<p><b>The need for optimization</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As time passes, your WordPress database can become unwieldy due to the garbage data it accumulates with each passing day. WP-Optimize removes this useless data, freeing up valuable megabytes while also increasing speed and efficiency. This plugin can also clean up your comments table, removing all the spam and un-approved comments that have built up &#8211; with just with a single click.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">WP-Optimize also gives you the option to use lazy loading for your WooCommerce store. Lazy loading is a function that allows your site to only load parts of a web-page when they are visible to the user, which results in faster loading pages. This allows the user to instantly start viewing the visible sections of the site, rather than wait for all the images and information on the page to load.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please note: It is highly recommended you first perform a backup of your site and WooCommerce store with </span><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/updraftplus/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UpdraftPlus</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> before you start setting up the optimization process.</span></p>\n<p><b>Optimize your WooCommerce Store</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To get started, get your copy of </span><a href=\"https://getwpo.com/buy\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">WP-Optimize</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and install it on your WordPress site.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next, head over to the </span><b>WP-Optimize&gt;Settings</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> page. Under &#8216;Database&#8217; you will see pre-selected options for optimization. Keep all pre-selected options as they are and click the &#8216;Run all selected optimizations&#8217; button.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-360820\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"724\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1.png 1600w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-300x136.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-768x348.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-1024x463.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-1080x489.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-510x231.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you would prefer to run each optimization separately, WP-Optimize also provides a &#8216;Run optimization&#8217; button next to each option.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next, under the &#8216;Images&#8217; section, you will see the orphaned image list &#8216;Unused images&#8217;. If you do not plan to use these orphaned images, then deleting them can save you valuable server space. To delete them, just select the images you wish to delete and hit the &#8216;Remove selected images&#8217; button.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-360821\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"621\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2.png 1600w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-300x116.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-768x298.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-1024x397.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-1080x419.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-510x198.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The final feature we recommend using is the previously mentioned &#8216;Lazyload&#8217; feature, which can help you speed up your WooCommerce store. To enable this setting, click on the &#8216;Lazyload&#8217; tab and tick both &#8216;Images&#8217; and &#8216;Iframes and Videos.&#8217;</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-360822\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1335\" height=\"461\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3.png 1335w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-300x104.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-768x265.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-1024x354.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-1080x373.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-510x176.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1335px) 100vw, 1335px\" /></a></p>\n<p><b>Conclusion</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speeding up your website can help your customers save time by making their purchases quicker and easier, resulting in happy customers that are more likely to return in the future and recommend your site to others. Try out the techniques techniques discussed and be sure to let us know how you get on in the comment section below.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-make-your-woocommerce-store-run-faster-with-wp-optimize/\">How to make your WooCommerce store run faster with WP-Optimize</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-make-your-woocommerce-store-run-faster-with-wp-optimize/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-make-your-woocommerce-store-run-faster-with-wp-optimize/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"UpdraftCentral announce new dashboard control of Incremental Backups with 0.8.5 release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/B4J4MBnGlHY/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:124:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral-announce-new-dashboard-control-of-incremental-backups-with-new-0-8-5-release/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 04 Mar 2019 14:23:41 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"UpdraftCentral\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"incremental backup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"incremental backups\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"UpdraftCental Update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"updraftcentral\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"updraftcentral development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=359048\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:901:\"<p>UpdraftCentral have released a brand new update: UpdraftCentral 0.8.5. This update comes with a great new feature and a couple of helpful tweaks. As you may have seen in our recently blogs, UpdraftPlus have recently launched Incremental Backups. This was a big &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral-announce-new-dashboard-control-of-incremental-backups-with-new-0-8-5-release/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral-announce-new-dashboard-control-of-incremental-backups-with-new-0-8-5-release/\">UpdraftCentral announce new dashboard control of Incremental Backups with 0.8.5 release</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"wmullins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2612:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UpdraftCentral have released a brand new update: UpdraftCentral 0.8.5. This update comes with a great new feature and a couple of helpful tweaks.</span></p>\n<p>As you may have seen in our recently blogs, UpdraftPlus have recently launched <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-launch-revoluntionary-new-incremental-backups-feature/\">Incremental Backups.</a> This was a big development in WordPress backups as it allows users to only update new changes that have occurred since the last backup, rather than starting a new full-site backup every time. This helps with the excessive resources which are used when performing a full site backup, which can also help users with low resource servers.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have been working hard to make Incremental Backups even more <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-use-incremental-backups/\">user friendly</a>, so the latest update of <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral/\">UpdraftCentral</a> allows users to control all their Incremental Backups from one place using the UpdraftCentral dashboard, available with <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/shop/updraftplus-premium/\">UpdraftPlus Premium</a>. You&#8217;ll be pleased to hear that this new feature means</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> no more switching back and forth between every single one of your sites every-time you want to schedule an Incremental Backup. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The changelog is as follows. We recommend the update for all users:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">FEATURE: Added the ability to take incremental backups</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">TWEAK: Updated bundled UDRPC library to version 1.4.17</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">TWEAK: Add more filters and docblocks to the licence manager class</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">TWEAK: Prevent a potential PHP notice when fetching cached site metadata</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral-announce-new-dashboard-control-of-incremental-backups-with-new-0-8-5-release/\">UpdraftCentral announce new dashboard control of Incremental Backups with 0.8.5 release</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:121:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral-announce-new-dashboard-control-of-incremental-backups-with-new-0-8-5-release/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:116:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral-announce-new-dashboard-control-of-incremental-backups-with-new-0-8-5-release/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"How to approve comments on all the sites you manage from one location using UpdraftCentral\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/As6xk4bp2Mw/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:123:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-approve-comments-on-all-the-sites-you-manage-from-one-location-using-updraftcentral/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 27 Feb 2019 12:31:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"UpdraftCentral\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"UpdraftCental Update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"updraftcentral\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"updraftcentral development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=357172\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:907:\"<p>Managing multiple WordPress websites can be challenging. It involves logging onto each dashboard separately, handle all the updates, manage comments and then carry out the operations. Faced with the same situation, our CEO David Anderson decided to do something about &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-approve-comments-on-all-the-sites-you-manage-from-one-location-using-updraftcentral/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-approve-comments-on-all-the-sites-you-manage-from-one-location-using-updraftcentral/\">How to approve comments on all the sites you manage from one location using UpdraftCentral</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Sajid Sayyad\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8822:\"<p>Managing multiple WordPress websites can be challenging. It involves logging onto each dashboard separately, handle all the updates, manage comments and then carry out the operations. Faced with the same situation, our CEO David Anderson decided to do something about it and created <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral\">UpdraftCentral</a> as part of the UpdraftPlus plugin.</p>\n<p>UpdraftCentral is a SaaS (Software as a Service) dashboard programme designed to manage multiple sites from one central location. Below are some of the major features &#8211;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Backup all your sites from one central location to the Cloud</li>\n<li>Manage and update all themes, plugins and WordPress core</li>\n<li>Automated backup schedule</li>\n<li>Manage users</li>\n<li>Manage comments</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can even try it for free! Yes, you heard that right! You can now manage <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/my-account/updraftcentral-remote-control/\">up to 5 sites</a> &#8211; free of charge on UpdraftCentral.</p>\n<p>Once you have created an account, you can access your dashboard at <i>https://updraftplus.com/my-account/updraftcentral-remote-control/</i></p>\n<p><strong>Adding a site to UpdraftCentral</strong></p>\n<p>Adding a site to your UpdraftCentral dashboard is quite simple. All you need to do is install the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/updraftplus/\">UpdraftPlus free</a> or <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/shop/updraftplus-premium/\">UpdraftPlus Premium</a> plugin on your WordPress site. The premium version of UpdraftPlus comes with several handy features that are not available with the free version. If you would like to read more about the comparison between both the free and premium versions, please click <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/comparison-updraftplus-free-updraftplus-premium\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>After you have installed and activated UpdraftPlus on your site, create an encrypted key that acts as the site identity on UpdraftCentral. Go to the &#8216;Advanced Tools&#8217; tab of UpdraftPlus setting page. On the left side, you see ‘UpdraftCentral’ &#8211; Click on it. You now see a section heading &#8211; “Connect this site to an….”.</p>\n<p>Inside you get a button &#8216;Updraftplus.com&#8217; &#8211; click on it.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-357176\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1421\" height=\"489\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1.png 1421w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1-300x103.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1-768x264.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1-1024x352.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1-1080x372.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1-510x176.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1421px) 100vw, 1421px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Next you will see a dropdown for ‘Encryption key size.’ Keep the default value as it is and click on the &#8216;Create&#8217; button.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-357181\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1038\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-1.png 1038w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-1-300x110.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-1-768x280.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-1-1024x374.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-1-510x186.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1038px) 100vw, 1038px\" /></a></p>\n<p>UpdraftPlus creates an encrypted key for UpdraftCentral.</p>\n<p>Now head over to your UpdraftCentral dashboard at <i>https://updraftplus.com/my-account/updraftcentral-remote-control/</i>.</p>\n<p>Go to &#8216;Sites&#8217; and click on the &#8216;+&#8217; icon in the top-right corner.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-357182\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1213\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1.png 1213w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1-300x94.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1-768x240.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1-1024x320.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1-1080x337.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1-510x159.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1213px) 100vw, 1213px\" /></a></p>\n<p>This opens a pop-up where you can paste your key. Once you have added the key, you will see your site listed under UpdraftCentral. Repeat the same process for any other sites you may want to add to UpdraftCentral.</p>\n<p><strong>How to Approve Comments Using UpdraftCentral</strong></p>\n<p>With UpdraftCentral, you can efficiently manage all of the comments from all of your sites from one central location. Posted comments automatically sync to the UpdraftCentral dashboard in the background. You can then carry out all the same operations that WordPress provides for comments such as &#8211; approve or disapprove comments, reply to comments, edit or trash the comment or mark as spam.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at UpdraftCentral in action. First, go to the &#8216;Comments&#8217; section of your UpdraftCentral dashboard.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-357193\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1179\" height=\"744\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1.png 1179w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1-300x189.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1-768x485.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1-1024x646.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1-1080x682.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1-510x322.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1179px) 100vw, 1179px\" /></a></p>\n<p>In this section, you get a list of all of your connected sites along with the options &#8216;Show Comments&#8217; and &#8216;Configure.&#8217; You can configure all of the comments settings by clicking on &#8216;Configure&#8217; which opens a pop-up window from where you can choose the settings.</p>\n<p>To approve comments click on &#8216;Show Comments,&#8217; after which you get a list of all the comments your site has received. You can view details including comment author, comment date and comments article. To approve a comment, click the &#8216;Approve Comment&#8217; button, which will automatically publishes the comment on your site.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-357194\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"779\" height=\"492\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-1.png 779w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-1-300x189.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-1-768x485.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-1-510x322.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 779px) 100vw, 779px\" /></a></p>\n<p>You can then perform the same process and approve comments on your other UpdraftCentral connected sites from the dashboard.</p>\n<p>Join <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral\">UpdraftCentral</a> for free and to start taking advantage of these amazing time-saving features.</p>\n<p>You can also read more about how UpdraftCentral will now allow you to install a new plugin or theme on all your WordPress sites at one <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftcentral-now-allows-you-to-install-a-new-plugin-or-theme-on-all-your-wordpress-sites-at-once/\">here</a> and about David’s journey with UpdraftCentral in this <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/interview-with-david-anderson-on-updraftcentral\">exclusive interview.</a></p>\n<p>Be sure to let us know any feedback comments you may have in the comment section below.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-approve-comments-on-all-the-sites-you-manage-from-one-location-using-updraftcentral/\">How to approve comments on all the sites you manage from one location using UpdraftCentral</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:120:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-approve-comments-on-all-the-sites-you-manage-from-one-location-using-updraftcentral/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:115:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-approve-comments-on-all-the-sites-you-manage-from-one-location-using-updraftcentral/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"How to clone or migrate a WooCommerce WordPress store automatically using UpdraftPlus\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/Wx2oUwu2UJ4/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:119:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-clone-or-migrate-a-woocommerce-wordpress-store-automatically-using-updraftplus/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 19 Feb 2019 15:04:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"UpdraftPlus advantages\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Clone WooCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Migrate WooCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"migration\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Migrator\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"UpdraftClone\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"Updraftplus migrator\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=351850\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:886:\"<p>Running a WooCommerce store is not easy. Your store’s plugins, themes, WordPress version and WooCommerce all need regular updates, which are highly recommended as they can help improve your overall store functionality. But making changes on the live store can &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-clone-or-migrate-a-woocommerce-wordpress-store-automatically-using-updraftplus/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-clone-or-migrate-a-woocommerce-wordpress-store-automatically-using-updraftplus/\">How to clone or migrate a WooCommerce WordPress store automatically using UpdraftPlus</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Sajid Sayyad\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12018:\"<p>Running a WooCommerce store is not easy. Your store’s plugins, themes, WordPress version and WooCommerce all need regular updates, which are highly recommended as they can help improve your overall store functionality.</p>\n<p>But making changes on the live store can be problematic &#8211; especially in case of new updates and features. Migrator lets you clone a site by creating an operational copy, providing a safe environment that allows you to test the latest updates and changes. This method ensures you avoid any kind of crash or unexpected behaviour when you make the actual live updates.</p>\n<p>Used by hundreds of thousands of WordPress sites UpdraftPlus Migrator (a feature of the UpdraftPlus plugin) is the world’s most trusted tool to clone your WooCommerce store in just a few clicks. The best part is, you can do it all from the WordPress dashboard itself.</p>\n<p><strong>Getting Started</strong></p>\n<p>First,  ensure the UpdraftPlus plugin is installed on your site. If you want to create a copied site with Migrator using the free version of UpdraftPlus, you will either need UpdraftPlus Premium or Migrator.</p>\n<p>Before you start, make sure you turn off any proxies that are between you and your site, such as Cloudflare, GoDaddy&#8217;s &#8220;Preview DNS&#8221; proxy or Opera Turbo/Road mode as these can potentially interfere with the clone process. Caching and minifying plugins are also a possible cause of migration problems. If possible, disable these before you create your backup – or alternatively, turn them off if the migration stumbles.</p>\n<p>Please follow these steps:</p>\n<p>To keep it simple we will use the following source and destination site.</p>\n<p><strong>Source site</strong> : <i>http://localhost/wc</i></p>\n<p><strong>Destination Site</strong> : <i>http://localhost/wcclone</i></p>\n<p>Ensure that the destination site has a fresh copy of WordPress installed on it. The source site will be your WooCommerce store.</p>\n<p><strong>Clone a WooCommerce store using UpdraftPlus Migrator</strong></p>\n<p>First, ensure that UpdraftPlus Migrator is present on both the source and the destination site.</p>\n<p>Go to the &#8216;Migrate/Clone&#8217; tab of your destination site. Click on the &#8216;Receive a backup from a remote site&#8217; button to open settings.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351859\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1047\" height=\"277\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1.png 1047w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-300x79.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-768x203.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-1024x271.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-510x135.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1047px) 100vw, 1047px\" /></a></p>\n<p>You do not need to change any settings. Click on the &#8216;Create Key&#8217; button.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-351860\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"778\" height=\"228\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.png 512w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-300x88.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-510x149.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 778px) 100vw, 778px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Copy the generated key as this will be required soon.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351862\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"963\" height=\"409\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.png 963w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-300x127.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-768x326.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-510x217.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 963px) 100vw, 963px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Next, head over to the source site and go to the &#8216;Migrate/Clone&#8217; tab. Click on the button &#8216;Send a backup to another site&#8217;.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351863\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1019\" height=\"282\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.png 1019w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-300x83.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-768x213.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-510x141.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1019px) 100vw, 1019px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Click on the &#8216;Add a site&#8217; link and paste the site key that you just copied from destination site.</p>\n<p>Next, click the &#8216;Add a site&#8217; button.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351864\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"972\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5.png 972w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-300x91.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-768x234.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-510x155.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 972px) 100vw, 972px\" /></a></p>\n<p>You should now see the destination site URL and a &#8216;Send&#8217; button. Click the &#8216;Send&#8217; button.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351865\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"803\" height=\"282\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6.png 803w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6-300x105.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6-768x270.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6-510x179.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 803px) 100vw, 803px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Next, you will be asked to select the options that you want to clone. Typically you need to choose all options except &#8216;WordPress core&#8217; as we have already installed WordPress on our destination site.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351867\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"754\" height=\"462\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7.png 754w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7-300x184.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7-510x312.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px\" /></a></p>\n<p>One you have ticked all the options required, click the &#8216;Send&#8217; button. UpdraftPlus will now start the process of migrating your site to the destination site. This will take some time depending on the size of your online store. After completion of the process, you should see the backup set in &#8216;Existing Backups&#8217;.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351872\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8.png 1600w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8-300x51.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8-768x132.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8-1024x175.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8-1080x185.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/8-510x87.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>This indicates that the source site has successfully sent a backup set to the destination site.</p>\n<p><strong>Restore the backup on the destination site</strong></p>\n<p>Once you have completed the above steps, head over to the destination site. In the &#8216;Existing Backups&#8217;, you will now see the backup set which was sent by your source site (your WooCommerce store).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351873\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9.png 1600w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9-300x52.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9-768x132.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9-1024x176.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9-1080x186.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9-510x88.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Click the &#8216;Restore&#8217; button and then tick all options.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/10.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351875\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/10.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"711\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/10.png 840w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/10-300x254.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/10-768x650.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/10-510x432.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Next, you will see a checkbox for database restoration options. Tick the checkbox and continue the process. As we are restoring the database of the source site, we need to update the URLs with the new site URLs.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/11.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351877\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/11.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"779\" height=\"674\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/11.png 779w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/11-300x260.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/11-768x664.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/11-510x441.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 779px) 100vw, 779px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Be patient and wait for UpdraftPlus to finish the process of migration. Once complete, log out of the dashboard.</p>\n<p>Login again and you will see your WooCommerce store has been cloned successfully.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12.png\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-351878\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1084\" height=\"446\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12.png 1600w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-300x123.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-768x316.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-1024x421.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-1080x444.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-510x210.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1084px) 100vw, 1084px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>In conclusion</strong></p>\n<p>Cloning a WooCommerce site might seem like a big task that requires a lot of technical expertise, but with UpdraftPlus Migrator you can simply and quickly clone your WooCommerce Store in just a few clicks.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-clone-or-migrate-a-woocommerce-wordpress-store-automatically-using-updraftplus/\">How to clone or migrate a WooCommerce WordPress store automatically using UpdraftPlus</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:115:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-clone-or-migrate-a-woocommerce-wordpress-store-automatically-using-updraftplus/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:110:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-clone-or-migrate-a-woocommerce-wordpress-store-automatically-using-updraftplus/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"Another Wordfence false positive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/cdRPSQe0B_I/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://updraftplus.com/another-wordfence-false-positive/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 18 Feb 2019 14:14:48 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"microsoft onedrive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=349867\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:781:\"<p>If you use Wordfence, and it is telling you that http://login.microsoftonline.de/common/oauth2/v2.0/authorize (found inside UpdraftPlus&#8217;s OneDrive code) is a phishing URL, then please rest assured that this is untrue. It is the official Office365 (including OneDrive) authentication URL for Microsoft Germany. &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/another-wordfence-false-positive/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/another-wordfence-false-positive/\">Another Wordfence false positive</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udadmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1389:\"<p>If you use Wordfence, and it is telling you that http://login.microsoftonline.de/common/oauth2/v2.0/authorize (found inside UpdraftPlus&#8217;s OneDrive code) is a phishing URL, then please rest assured that this is untrue. It is the official Office365 (including OneDrive) authentication URL for Microsoft Germany.<a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/office/enterprise-includes/o365endpoints/office-365-germany-endpoints\"> You can verify this at the official page on microsoft.com, here</a>.</p>\n<p>If you get this report, then <strong>please do report this to Wordfence if you can</strong>. The number of times that Wordfence flags false positives in different places is a non-trivial support burden (and last happened under two weeks ago), as well as surely being an annoyance to Wordfence users who value their time.</p>\n<p>We recommend that Wordfence users suggest to Wordfence support that they test all their anti-virus rules upon the most popular WordPress plugins before releasing them to their end-users.</p>\n<p>David Anderson (lead developer)</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/another-wordfence-false-positive/\">Another Wordfence false positive</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://updraftplus.com/another-wordfence-false-positive/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://updraftplus.com/another-wordfence-false-positive/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:117:\"UpdraftPlus announces features including a faster UpdraftPlus Clone and more reliable backups with new 1.16.6 release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/oRNmyUnYGBk/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-announces-features-including-a-faster-updraftplus-clone-and-more-reliable-backups-with-new-1-16-6-release/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 15 Feb 2019 14:28:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"UpdraftPlus development news\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Clone Update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"updraft plus\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"updraft plus development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=348788\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:950:\"<p>UpdraftPlus have been hard at work on the latest update and we are happy to announce that UpdraftPlus 1.16.6 has been released and is now available. For this update there’s a new feature which enables UpdraftPlus to send you an &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-announces-features-including-a-faster-updraftplus-clone-and-more-reliable-backups-with-new-1-16-6-release/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-announces-features-including-a-faster-updraftplus-clone-and-more-reliable-backups-with-new-1-16-6-release/\">UpdraftPlus announces features including a faster UpdraftPlus Clone and more reliable backups with new 1.16.6 release</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"wmullins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6189:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UpdraftPlus have been hard at work on the latest update and we are happy to announce that UpdraftPlus 1.16.6 has been released and is now available. For this update there’s a new feature which enables UpdraftPlus to send you an email report even if the backup fails. This will help users keep better track of their backup status and make sure that you are always up to date with the latest developments of your site.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have also made updates to UpdraftClone that has made the feature faster and more reliable, improving this popular service further.</span></p>\n<div id=\"attachment_348798\" style=\"width: 960px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-348798\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"950\" height=\"421\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4.jpg 1898w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4-300x133.jpg 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4-768x340.jpg 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4-1024x454.jpg 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4-1080x479.jpg 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-4-510x226.jpg 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 950px) 100vw, 950px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Improved performance from UpdraftClone</p></div>\n<p>Additional, we have made it much easier to users to purchase UpdraftPlus Premium from within the plugin. So instead of being forced to leave the plugin and purchase Premium via our website, you can now make the purchase from within the plugin, saving you a lot of time and trouble.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_348792\" style=\"width: 960px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-348792\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"950\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3.jpg 1883w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3-300x118.jpg 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3-768x303.jpg 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3-1024x404.jpg 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3-1080x426.jpg 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/New-Project-3-510x201.jpg 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 950px) 100vw, 950px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">You can now purchase Premium from within the plugin</p></div>\n<p>We recommend the update for all UpdraftPlus users.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The full change-log is as follows;</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>FEATURE</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Added new S3 intelligent tiering class</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>FEATURE</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ability for user to buy Premium without leaving the plugin&#8217;s settings pages</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>FEATURE</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: UpdraftPlus can now catch backups that don&#8217;t complete because of errors that kill PHP and make sure a report is still sent about them. This ensures that you will get an email, even if the backup fails.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>FIX</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: If a very large UpdraftVault upload took more than an hour, then the token could expire without being refreshed (fix in version 1.16.0 was incomplete)</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>PERFORMANCE</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Modify a condition in the zip-batching algorithm so that greater acceleration in the zip-batching algorithm is allowed on setups allowing very long PHP run times on the initial (zero-eth) resumption</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>PERFORMANCE</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: UpdraftClone now sends larger chunks over the network, leading to faster sending of data</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>PERFORMANCE</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Force UpdraftClone to use a 100MB split size for better performance (previously intended, but not always working)</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>TWEAK</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Upon restoration, WP&#8217;s cache directory will be emptied (by default it is not included in backups, so in theory this is a no-op, but the occasional case has been seen where it got populated during the restore process)</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>TWEAK</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Add support for the new Europe (Stockholm) (eu-north-1) AWS region in Amazon S3</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>TWEAK</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Advise the user if they changed the plugin&#8217;s slug (and so won&#8217;t be able to get updates) (paid versions)</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>TWEAK</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Make use of wp_get_themes rather than relying solely to get_themes which is already deprecated</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>TWEAK</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Regression: When a user aborted a fatal error occurred before all clean-up actions were complete</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>TWEAK</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Refactor the remote storage logging code in Backblaze and Azure modules</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"mceTemp\"></div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-announces-features-including-a-faster-updraftplus-clone-and-more-reliable-backups-with-new-1-16-6-release/\">UpdraftPlus announces features including a faster UpdraftPlus Clone and more reliable backups with new 1.16.6 release</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:147:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-announces-features-including-a-faster-updraftplus-clone-and-more-reliable-backups-with-new-1-16-6-release/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:142:\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-announces-features-including-a-faster-updraftplus-clone-and-more-reliable-backups-with-new-1-16-6-release/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"How to restore a ‘BackupWordPress’ backup using UpdraftPlus Premium\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/Q1UUNg3amuw/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-restore-a-backupwordpress-backup-using-updraftplus-premium/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 13 Feb 2019 10:55:55 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"UpdraftPlus advantages\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"backupwordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"updraftplus backup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"UpdraftPlus development\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"using backupwordpress on updraftplus\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=347975\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:821:\"<p>With 2 million+ active installs, UpdraftPlus is one of the most popular and trusted WordPress backup plugins currently on the market. The popularity of the plugin is due to its simplicity and wide variety of features, including the ability to &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-restore-a-backupwordpress-backup-using-updraftplus-premium/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-restore-a-backupwordpress-backup-using-updraftplus-premium/\">How to restore a &#8216;BackupWordPress&#8217; backup using UpdraftPlus Premium</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Sajid Sayyad\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6476:\"<p>With 2 million+ active installs, UpdraftPlus is one of the most popular and trusted WordPress backup plugins currently on the market. The popularity of the plugin is due to its simplicity and wide variety of features, including the ability to restore backups created by other backup plugins, such as BackupWordPress.</p>\n<p>However, unlike UpdraftPlus, BackupWordPress does not give the user an automatic restore option. This mean BackupWordPress users are forced to restore their sites manually by uploading all your files and folders via FTP and importing the database using phpMyAdmin. This task can be painstakingly dull and complicated, even for someone with developer experience.</p>\n<p><strong>Restoring your backup using UpdraftPlus Premium</strong></p>\n<p>Fortunately, there is a great solution to help users restore their BackupWordPress backups using UpdraftPlus Premium. Please be aware that you can use the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/updraftplus\">UpdraftPlus free</a> version do a basic restore but if you want to restore from a BackupWordpress backup, this feature is only available with the <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/shop\">UpdraftPlus Premium</a> plugin.</p>\n<p>Note: The Premium version of UpdraftPlus has many other useful features, which you can read about <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-full-feature-list\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Once you have installed and activated the UpdraftPlus Premium plugin, it is a relatively straightforward process to use one of the two methods to add and run your BackupWordPress backups to UpdraftPlus.</p>\n<h3>Method 1</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The first step is to find the backup files. BackupWordPress plugin creates a directory with prefix <code>backupwordpress-</code> inside the <code>wp-content</code> directory.<a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-directory.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-348395 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-directory.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"468\" height=\"218\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-directory.png 468w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-directory-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 468px) 100vw, 468px\" /></a></li>\n<li>All the backups made by the BackupWordPress plugin are saved inside this directory. Our example is shown below:<a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-backups.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-348396 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-backups.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"676\" height=\"291\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-backups.png 676w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-backups-300x129.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/backupwordpress-backups-510x220.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 676px) 100vw, 676px\" /></a></li>\n<li>Copy your backup zip files from the above directory and paste it inside the <code>wp-content/updraft</code> folder.</li>\n<li>Next, go to the settings page of UpdraftPlus. Click on the &#8216;Rescan local folder’ for new backup sets&#8217; link. This will rescan the <code>wp-content/updraft</code> directory and add new backups within &#8216;Existing Backups&#8217;.<a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-348398 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"680\" height=\"93\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed.png 512w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-300x41.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-510x70.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px\" /></a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-1.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-348399 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"802\" height=\"188\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-1.png 512w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-1-300x70.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-1-510x120.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 802px) 100vw, 802px\" /></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>If everything worked, your new backup files will now be visible in the list. You can now restore your backups and also use the other useful features provided by the UpdraftPlus Premium plugin. You can also upload this backup to remote storage if required.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Method 2</h3>\n<p>This method is almost the same the first, but instead of copy/pasting your backup files, you can upload your BackupWordPress backup file to the &#8216;Existing Backups&#8217; list.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>On the UpdraftPlus settings page, click &#8216;Upload backup file&#8217;.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-2.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-348400 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"845\" height=\"259\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-2.png 512w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-2-300x92.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/unnamed-2-510x156.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 845px) 100vw, 845px\" /></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Next, choose the locally stored backup file.</li>\n<li>After the upload process is complete, your backup will be present in the &#8216;Existing Backups&#8217; list.</li>\n<li>Once the backup is present in the UpdraftPlus list, you can select it and click the restore button. In just a few minutes you should have restored your files and database.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That&#8217;s it for this tutorial! We hope this explains everything you needed to know on how to add and restore a BackupWordPress backup using UpdraftPlus Premium.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, please let us know in the comments below.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-restore-a-backupwordpress-backup-using-updraftplus-premium/\">How to restore a &#8216;BackupWordPress&#8217; backup using UpdraftPlus Premium</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-restore-a-backupwordpress-backup-using-updraftplus-premium/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-restore-a-backupwordpress-backup-using-updraftplus-premium/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"WP-Optimize 2.2.12 now released\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/o_mIUa5EI5A/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize2-2-12-now-released/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 08 Feb 2019 15:17:46 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP Optimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"WP-O\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP-Optimise\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WP-Optimise Update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP-Optimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"WP-Optmize update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=346504\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:703:\"<p>We are pleased to announce that we have released an updated version of WP-Optimize 2.2.12 for both free and paid versions. We recommend the update for all WP-Optimize users. The full changelog is as follows; TWEAK: Updated information on More &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize2-2-12-now-released/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize2-2-12-now-released/\">WP-Optimize 2.2.12 now released</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"wmullins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2221:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We are pleased to announce that we have released an updated version of WP-Optimize 2.2.12 for both free and paid versions.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We recommend the update for all WP-Optimize users.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The full changelog is as follows;</span></p>\n<ul style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>TWEAK</strong>: Updated information on More plugins tab</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>TWEAK</strong>: Fix header layout when a system or third party notification are shown</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>TWEAK</strong>: (Premium) Fix layout in unused images list mode</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>TWEAK</strong>: Improve data reliability in javascript</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>TWEAK</strong>: Improve orphaned relationships data optimization</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>TWEAK</strong>: Wrong message for “remove spam and trashed comments” optimization</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>TWEAK</strong>: Output additional information if table was not deleted</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>FIX</strong>: Added escaping for table names in database queries</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>FIX</strong>: Fix another possible fatal error due to missing get_plugins() function</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>FIX</strong>: Improve identification of installed/active plugins</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize2-2-12-now-released/\">WP-Optimize 2.2.12 now released</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize2-2-12-now-released/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize2-2-12-now-released/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:39:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/UpdraftPlus\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:3:\"rel\";s:3:\"hub\";s:4:\"href\";s:32:\"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.